24:03.792 --> 24:06.420
<i>Eye to eye you are no match</i>

24:06.628 --> 24:09.256
<i>'Cause you wanna fall in love</i>

24:10.507 --> 24:13.135
<i>Girls, he'll break your heart</i>

24:13.343 --> 24:15.220
<i>Do you wrong, tell you lies</i>

24:15.429 --> 24:18.558
<i>'Cause he's got those</i>

24:18.766 --> 24:21.736
<i>Far away eyes</i>

24:26.398 --> 24:29.948
<i>Far away eyes</i>

24:30.486 --> 24:33.535
<i>I'm a fool, baby</i>

24:33.739 --> 24:37.369
<i>Far away eyes</i>

24:39.995 --> 24:42.498
<i>Boy, you're a heartbreaker</i>

24:42.706 --> 24:45.459
<i>Still, I've got to make you mine</i>

24:45.667 --> 24:47.590
<i>Play on this, baby</i>

24:47.795 --> 24:50.173
(SINGER MOANING)

24:55.219 --> 24:57.392
<i>You're the one and only</i>

24:57.596 --> 24:59.269
<i>Open up my door</i>

24:59.473 --> 25:02.943
<i>And love me with your</i>

25:03.143 --> 25:07.023
<i>Far away eyes</i>

25:10.526 --> 25:14.247
<i>Far away eyes</i>

25:14.655 --> 25:17.659
<i>How do you feel, baby</i>

25:17.866 --> 25:21.712
<i>Far away eyes</i>

25:24.081 --> 25:26.709
<i>Boy, you're a heartbreaker</i>

25:26.917 --> 25:30.296
<i>Still, I've got to make you mine</i>

25:31.755 --> 25:34.554
I expected a standing ovation.

25:34.758 --> 25:36.101
You're getting one.

25:45.936 --> 25:49.031
- Will you be leaving now, Miss Ash?
- Yes, she will, Edd.

25:49.857 --> 25:51.484
Would you like me to accompany you?

25:51.900 --> 25:54.403
No, thank you.
This part I can do on my own.

25:59.700 --> 26:01.919
You remember who
pays your salary?

26:02.119 --> 26:05.089
You do, Mr. Dellaplane.
And most generously.

26:05.831 --> 26:07.128
Right.

26:15.048 --> 26:18.598
Working for Springer,
my job was to keep tabs on people.

26:18.802 --> 26:22.898
Ask questions, find out who's planning
what power plays. That kind of thing.

26:23.182 --> 26:24.934
Dellaplane, he was...

26:25.225 --> 26:29.480
working his way through the union.
Finding who's for him, who against.

26:29.688 --> 26:34.444
Who resented his money, his power.
Who was agreeing with him...

26:34.651 --> 26:37.700
and, uh, it was all that.
JACKSON: All right, look.

26:37.905 --> 26:39.999
What does that have
to do with Stringer?

26:40.532 --> 26:41.954
Stringer didn't trust him.

26:42.159 --> 26:43.752
He hated his guts, in fact.

26:43.952 --> 26:48.207
That's the same for Norman and
for Grantham. And because of that...

26:48.415 --> 26:50.793
Dellaplane wanted them
out of the way.

26:51.001 --> 26:52.469
For what?

26:55.172 --> 26:57.675
That's the rickety part,
because I don't know.

26:58.717 --> 27:00.845
It's just, heh...
I can't figure that out.

27:01.053 --> 27:03.351
Wait.
Come on, think about it.

27:04.014 --> 27:06.984
You're saying Dellaplane's killing
off unfriendly AWA leaders...

27:07.184 --> 27:10.279
and you don't know why and
you don't have any evidence.

27:10.479 --> 27:13.198
Don't tell me you're
afraid of Dellaplane.

27:13.398 --> 27:15.821
The Jackson I knew
wasn't afraid of nothing.

27:16.026 --> 27:18.700
We all thought he'd make
a name for himself.

27:20.155 --> 27:22.157
If I got the wrong Jackson,
please tell me.

27:22.366 --> 27:24.869
Come on, you got the right Jackson.

27:26.995 --> 27:30.090
He didn't make the name for himself
he thought he would.

27:31.875 --> 27:34.003
One person you might try...

27:34.962 --> 27:37.715
is Dellaplane's mistress.
She's a singer.

27:38.215 --> 27:41.435
Her name is Sydney Ash
and she works at this club.

27:41.635 --> 27:45.515
Joey's Club Elite.
All right?

27:47.391 --> 27:49.564
- I'm not wasting your time.
- I know.

27:49.768 --> 27:52.362
I promise you that
I'm on to something.

27:52.562 --> 27:53.609
Thanks.

27:54.356 --> 27:56.358
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

28:16.169 --> 28:18.137
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

28:19.548 --> 28:20.891
Moretti?

28:22.009 --> 28:23.431
Delivery.

28:31.435 --> 28:33.358
Would you please sign here?

28:37.691 --> 28:39.113
It's C.O.D.

28:42.237 --> 28:43.784
(CHUCKLES)

28:46.450 --> 28:49.249
I saw your wife in the
paper last week.

28:49.453 --> 28:52.127
Are you ever gonna
tell her about me?

28:55.083 --> 28:57.632
- Why would I do a thing like that?
- Hmm.

28:57.836 --> 29:00.635
You know I never mix
business with pleasure.

29:00.839 --> 29:03.843
Which of us is business
and which is pleasure, huh?

29:04.051 --> 29:06.349
Would you like me to
spell it out for you?

29:07.179 --> 29:10.729
- You said that you'd come see me more.
- Hmm.

29:11.767 --> 29:15.988
And you said a man from Motown
was gonna come hear me sing.

29:16.188 --> 29:18.441
DELLAPLANE: Mm-hm.
SYDNEY: Mm-hm.

29:18.648 --> 29:21.447
And you also said that
I could cut a record...

29:21.651 --> 29:24.200
and that I'd be going places.
- Hmm.

29:24.404 --> 29:26.077
SYDNEY: Mm-hm.

29:26.615 --> 29:28.162
DELLAPLANE: Hmm.

29:28.658 --> 29:30.956
Did I say all that?

29:31.870 --> 29:32.917
Mm-hm.

29:33.121 --> 29:34.919
- Really?
- Mm-hm.

29:35.123 --> 29:38.377
Give me two good reasons why
I'd say all those things.

29:41.338 --> 29:43.932
Oh, yeah.
Now I remember.

29:44.132 --> 29:46.226
Oh, baby.

29:46.426 --> 29:47.643
(SYDNEY CHUCKLES)

29:47.844 --> 29:49.846
You're gorgeous.

29:59.314 --> 30:00.657
This...

30:01.274 --> 30:04.653
is supposed to be
a girl's best friend.

30:08.198 --> 30:10.951
What would I ever do
without you, huh?

30:18.250 --> 30:20.719
Let's hope you never
have to find out.

30:24.840 --> 30:26.842
(SYDNEY MOANING)

30:31.054 --> 30:32.226
Sweet dreams, baby.

30:40.021 --> 30:43.366
MORTY: Amphetamines,
malnutrition, insomnia.

30:43.567 --> 30:47.367
If the bullet hadn't gotten him, he
would've dropped dead within the week.

30:47.571 --> 30:50.324
That's very consoling.
You got a great bedside manner.

30:50.532 --> 30:54.753
In this business, I need a bedside
manner like I need another nose.

30:56.413 --> 30:58.131
He's a friend of yours, huh?

30:58.331 --> 31:01.551
From the same high school.
We were on the track team together.

31:01.751 --> 31:03.219
He was a high-strung kid.

31:03.420 --> 31:07.345
I hadn't seen much of him since
he started to work for the union.

31:07.549 --> 31:09.301
Kotterwell says it's suicide.

31:09.509 --> 31:12.888
He wouldn't know suicide if it
crawled up his ass and died there.

31:13.096 --> 31:14.188
(CHUCKLES)

31:14.389 --> 31:16.642
They said Tony killed himself
with a 9mm. Bullshit.

31:16.850 --> 31:19.979
I saw him packing a .32.
Somebody planted that 9mm on him.

31:20.187 --> 31:21.655
You got any leads?

31:21.855 --> 31:26.531
I know a woman who might help, but I
gotta get her away from her husband.

31:26.693 --> 31:28.570
- Ooh. Story of my life.
- Heh.

31:28.987 --> 31:31.706
FOSS: All right. But if I see
a cake with 63 candles...

31:31.907 --> 31:35.787
I'll be out the door faster
than shit through Secretariat.

31:35.952 --> 31:37.295
(DELLAPLANE CHUCKLES)

31:37.454 --> 31:39.331
JACKSON:
This should go well with your meal.

31:46.254 --> 31:49.258
I didn't know you listed photography
among your interests.

31:49.466 --> 31:50.934
Is that all you have to say?

31:51.134 --> 31:53.353
The negative's quite poor,
isn't it?

31:55.430 --> 31:57.979
The quality of the print
seems excellent.

31:58.183 --> 32:01.062
It's a shame the subject
wasn't more cooperative.

32:01.269 --> 32:03.488
- Who was he?
- His name was Tony Moretti.

32:03.688 --> 32:06.692
He worked for Stringer.
They knew your plans for the AWA...

32:06.900 --> 32:09.744
and now they're both dead.
Is that clear enough?

32:09.945 --> 32:12.118
What are you planning for the AWA?

32:12.322 --> 32:14.495
Ray, I'm sorry. My manners are...

32:14.699 --> 32:16.042
Sweetheart.

32:16.451 --> 32:20.081
This is Sergeant Jericho Jackson,
one of Detroit's finest.

32:20.288 --> 32:23.918
This is Raymond Foss,
president of the Auto Workers Alliance.

32:24.125 --> 32:28.505
I'm sure he would be delighted
to hear what I have planned.

32:30.257 --> 32:32.510
- Good afternoon, Mr. Foss.
- Sergeant.

32:32.717 --> 32:36.597
Too bad you couldn't find a more
suitable luncheon companion.

32:38.014 --> 32:41.439
Mrs. Dellaplane,
I hope you'll forgive the intrusion.

32:42.227 --> 32:43.570
Good day.

32:44.938 --> 32:46.781
Is he giving you trouble?

32:48.066 --> 32:51.320
His kind of trouble
is no trouble at all.

32:54.906 --> 32:56.783
(GRUNTING AND YELLING)

33:30.025 --> 33:32.027
(MAN COUGHS AND GROANS)

33:45.290 --> 33:46.963
Lesson's over.

33:48.293 --> 33:49.920
Show him to his car.

33:50.128 --> 33:51.755
(MAN GROANING)

35:00.782 --> 35:02.284
(CHATTERING)

35:08.039 --> 35:10.508
CARTIER: We're having some
problems with O'Rooney...

35:10.709 --> 35:13.462
but we should have him
in shape by this Sunday.

35:15.797 --> 35:18.846
Jackson got to Moretti
before we did.

35:19.050 --> 35:22.145
It doesn't matter.
What could he tell him? He had no proof.

35:23.012 --> 35:26.437
Jackson? No need to.
He doesn't know enough...

35:32.731 --> 35:35.780
I say that sounds fine.
I believe we can meet that.

35:35.984 --> 35:37.702
Peter, I need to talk to you.

35:37.902 --> 35:41.372
I got a meeting in 14 minutes.
I'm on the phone to Italy.

35:41.573 --> 35:43.871
It costs more than
your diamond brooch.

35:44.075 --> 35:46.043
- It's important.
- This is important.

35:46.244 --> 35:48.713
I say we can meet that.
Let's go, please.

35:48.913 --> 35:51.166
It'll just take a second, honey...

35:51.791 --> 35:54.294
It'll be about a couple
of weeks, I think.

36:01.092 --> 36:04.221
Will you be leaving, madam?
I'll be happy to drive you.

36:04.429 --> 36:06.773
No, thank you.
I can do it myself.

36:08.433 --> 36:10.902
- Sergeant.
- I was just coming to see you.

36:11.102 --> 36:13.981
- Are you going into town?
- I am. Would you like a ride?

36:14.773 --> 36:16.867
I thought you'd never ask.

36:39.589 --> 36:42.263
SYDNEY: I couldn't figure out what
they were talking about...

36:42.467 --> 36:44.515
but I heard him say
the name Moretti.

36:44.719 --> 36:46.972
And he definitely said your name.

36:50.058 --> 36:52.231
He also mentioned
a man named O'Rooney.

36:52.435 --> 36:56.656
How they were having trouble with him,
but they'd have him in shape by Sunday.

36:56.856 --> 36:58.699
That's gotta be Oliver O'Rooney.

36:59.400 --> 37:03.450
He used to work for your husband,
but now he's with the AWA.

37:03.655 --> 37:05.749
- You familiar with the name?
- No.

37:05.949 --> 37:09.078
What do you know about
Frank Stringer or Lionel Grantham?

37:09.285 --> 37:11.287
Only what I read in the paper.

37:11.496 --> 37:15.501
Peter never mentioned them.
He doesn't bring his work home with him.

37:16.042 --> 37:20.138
Except this weekend. He's giving a
party for that man we had lunch with.

37:20.338 --> 37:23.182
Raymond Foss?
Aren't he and your husband friends?

37:23.383 --> 37:24.600
No, not at all.

37:24.801 --> 37:27.429
In fact, I could've sworn
they hated each other.

37:27.637 --> 37:29.935
He's gotta be used to that by now.

37:30.515 --> 37:34.816
I know how you feel about Peter.
But you don't know him the way I do.

37:35.520 --> 37:37.488
He may seem greedy and arrogant...

37:37.689 --> 37:40.863
but you don't make it big
and remained loved by everyone.

37:41.568 --> 37:46.165
I met him after his first wife died
and his son went to prison.

37:46.364 --> 37:48.913
I think the whole
experience changed him.

37:49.659 --> 37:52.253
He's not the man
you think you know.

37:53.955 --> 37:55.878
What do you think
you know about me?

37:57.083 --> 37:59.302
I think you're not
so different from Peter.

37:59.711 --> 38:03.557
You're both stubborn.
Both intent on getting what you want.

38:05.425 --> 38:08.975
You know, I think Peter
admires you a little bit.

38:09.512 --> 38:12.607
Not many people cause him
so much trouble and get away with it.

38:13.099 --> 38:15.397
Who says I've gotten away
with anything?

38:16.519 --> 38:17.771
Let's get out of here.

38:21.566 --> 38:24.740
- Can you get me into the party?
- Not and keep my marriage.

38:24.944 --> 38:27.538
Heh, I cut a fine figure
on the dance floor.

38:27.739 --> 38:31.084
At least I would, if your husband
didn't have my legs broken.

38:34.537 --> 38:36.460
Why do they call you Action...?

38:37.665 --> 38:39.588
(TIRES SCREECH)

38:42.170 --> 38:43.638
Are you okay?

38:43.922 --> 38:46.641
Go to the police station.
I have to catch a cab.

38:49.594 --> 38:51.312
MAN 1: Hey!
MAN 2: Hey, what are you doing?

38:58.895 --> 39:01.318
(ENGINE REVS AND TIRES SCREECH)

39:03.983 --> 39:05.405
(HORNS HONKING)

39:10.698 --> 39:13.326
Hey, you!
I'm talking to you!

39:15.078 --> 39:17.206
Come on, asshole!

39:22.627 --> 39:24.129
Now I got you!

39:37.475 --> 39:38.522
(YELLS)

39:38.726 --> 39:40.603
Maybe this wasn't
a good idea after all.

39:44.065 --> 39:45.658
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

40:11.634 --> 40:13.261
JACKSON: Shit.

40:13.636 --> 40:15.229
Oh, shit!

40:16.681 --> 40:17.898
Enough is enough!

40:29.652 --> 40:31.199
(GUN CLICKS)

40:31.404 --> 40:33.998
You want to shoot me?
I'm not packing. Don't shoot me!

40:34.198 --> 40:36.166
Come on! Come on and get me!

40:36.367 --> 40:38.119
Don't shoot me. That's too easy.

40:38.327 --> 40:40.250
Be a man!
Come and get me!

40:40.455 --> 40:44.085
I know you killed Tony!
Come on, chicken shit!

40:44.292 --> 40:45.464
Come on!

40:45.668 --> 40:47.045
(ENGINE REVS)

40:57.096 --> 40:58.439
(YELLS)

41:16.783 --> 41:18.080
(SIREN WAILING NEARBY)

41:20.578 --> 41:22.956
Son of a bitch. Shit.

41:23.915 --> 41:25.087
Where did he go?

41:37.220 --> 41:38.563
I'm afraid to ask.

41:39.430 --> 41:40.932
Uh, dry cleaning.

41:41.474 --> 41:44.318
- Ray Foss is on the line.
- I'll take it in my office.

41:44.519 --> 41:47.068
It's the Martinizing that does it.

41:49.857 --> 41:52.986
Did a woman come by for me?
Twenty-nine, a blond?

41:53.194 --> 41:55.617
Christ, I thought I dreamed.

41:55.822 --> 41:58.792
What the hell happened to you?
Wait.

41:58.991 --> 42:00.618
She left a note.

42:04.330 --> 42:07.800
"I'm gonna tell Peter everything."
Jackson, how do you do it?

42:09.418 --> 42:10.920
It's the clothes.

42:11.170 --> 42:12.797
ARMBRUSTER: What?

42:16.843 --> 42:18.311
Where the hell is Jackson?

42:22.348 --> 42:23.600
MAN: Ladies and gentlemen...

42:23.808 --> 42:26.687
Joey's Club Elite
is proud to present...

42:26.894 --> 42:28.487
Sydney Ash!

42:29.647 --> 42:31.320
(BAND PLAYING POP MUSIC)

42:35.820 --> 42:39.040
<i>(SINGING)
All my love is for your fun</i>

42:39.240 --> 42:42.210
<i>If you keep me up on the one</i>

42:44.120 --> 42:47.750
